sentences.english: Dianna is leaving for London tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 戴安娜明天将动身去伦敦。

sentences.english: Ann's friendliness with Diana is only skin-deep.
sentences.chinese: 安与戴安娜的友谊只是表面的。
戴安娜轻轻颤抖了一下。

sentences.english: Both Joe and Diana are very good in sports.
sentences.chinese: 吉欧和戴安娜两人都擅长运动。

sentences.english: She’s 29, nine years older than Diana was when she married.
sentences.chinese: 比戴安娜王妃结婚时大了9岁。

sentences.english: Hi! My name is Diana but you can call me "Yans".
sentences.chinese: 嗨，我叫戴安娜，你也可以称呼我Yans。

sentences.english: He has deciphered Diana's "Let's" as a command.
sentences.chinese: 他把戴安娜的“让我们”理解为命令。

sentences.english: Diana always says that he has a hot bod!
sentences.chinese: 戴安娜总是说他是一个火热的娃。

sentences.english: Diana was not short of wit or dignity or a sense of duty.
sentences.chinese: 戴安娜一点也不缺乏智慧，尊严和责任感。

sentences.english: Princess Diana's Memorial is actually a fountain.
sentences.chinese: 戴安娜王妃纪念碑是一个水泉池。

sentences.english: Three days after he was back, he arranged to see Diana at Windsor Castle.
sentences.chinese: 三天后，他回来了，他被安排见戴安娜在温莎堡。

sentences.english: Oddly, there is also a Princess Diana commemoration set.
sentences.chinese: 怪的是，竟然还有一套纪念戴安娜王妃的邮票。

sentences.english: Then he looks through the doorway, into the bedroom.
sentences.chinese: 他的视线穿过卧室门口，看到了戴安娜。

sentences.english: Diana told Prince Charles over and over that she loved him.
sentences.chinese: 戴安娜一遍又一遍地对王子说她爱他。

sentences.english: Diana was the godmother of Mrs Moncktons daughter Domenica.
sentences.chinese: 戴安娜还是蒙克顿夫人的女儿多梅尼卡的教母。
